# ===== CANAL-AI .gitignore =====
# Protects patient data, credentials, internal planning docs, and the
# identities of potential / current collaborators. This repository is
# public; anything sensitive must stay local.

# ----- Patient data (NEVER commit) -----
data/*
!data/README.md
!data/.gitkeep

# Local extracts, parquet/fst caches, pickles
*.parquet
*.fst
*.rds
*.rda
*.RData
*.pkl
*.joblib

# ----- Output (commit README / .gitkeep only; review before committing anything else) -----
output/*
!output/README.md
!output/.gitkeep

# ----- Internal documentation (names of participants, plans, status) -----
# Everything under docs/ is internal by default. Only the public README is
# tracked. To publish a doc, explicitly un-ignore it below.
docs/*
!docs/README.md

# Common internal-doc filename patterns, in case they live elsewhere
**/plan.md
**/PLAN.md
**/*_plan.md
**/*_PLAN.md
**/roadmap_internal.md
**/team_internal.md
**/participants.md
**/PARTICIPANTS.md
**/contacts.md
**/CONTACTS.md
**/charter_internal.md
**/context_for_claude*.md
**/00_context*.md

# ----- Admin / institutional correspondence (never public) -----
admin/*
!admin/README.md

# ----- Credentials and site-specific config -----
config.yml
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem
credentials.json
secrets.yml

# ----- R / RStudio -----
.Rproj.user/
.Rhistory
.RData
.Ruserdata
*.Rproj.user
renv/library/
renv/local/
renv/cellar/
renv/staging/
# keep renv.lock tracked (project-wide reproducibility)

# ----- Python -----
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.venv/
venv/
.env/
env/
*.egg-info/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ----- OS cruft -----
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
ehthumbs.db

# ----- Editors -----
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ----- Logs and temp -----
*.log
tmp/
temp/

# ----- Built docs / site build artefacts -----
docs/_site/
docs/_book/
site/_site/
_site/
*.html.aux
